We plan for 5 minutes per item and it always seems to work perfectly.
We also arrange for the last-but-one in a set to de disposable so if we
get an early &quot;one more&quot; signal we can skip that one and always finish
with the planned grand finale.

I'd like to be able to do it by watching the clock, but I can't trust
myself to remember to do that. Also it doesn't look good on stage to
keep looking at your watch :-)

I'd have thought good timing was an obvious part of professionalism and
vice versa and can't understand why anyone would want to overrun. Given
the choice: (a) Leave them wanting more or (b) look amateurish and out
of control - it's a no-brainer!

